    .groupsite_blue.subtitle.is-3[data-search-target="result"]
      |  Pricing 
    .groupsite_blue.subtitle.is-5[data-search-target="result"]
      |  There are two account types. Enterprise and regular. 
    ol
      li[data-search-target="result"]
        |  Regular account the cost is $99 per month or $990 annually. This package includes 1 groupsite, 4 managers for the groupsite, unlimited users, 40GB of storage space, 4 subgroups. For an additional $10 a month or $100 yearly the following would be added to the groupsite 1 manager, 10GB of storage, and 1 subgroup. Upgrading one would upgrade all 3. Managers can add as many upgrades as needed. 
      li[data-search-target="result"]
        |  Enterprise account - Contact 
        a[href="mailto:billing@groupsite.com"]
          |  billing@groupsite.com
        |  for a package that works for your needs. Enterprise accounts would include multiple groupsites under one account. More information can be found by going to groupsite.com/pricing and scrolling down to the section "Groupsite Enterprise Platform". Here you will see a list of full packages available and pricing. These packages can be downgraded and adjusted to fit your budget and needs. 
    
    .groupsite_blue.subtitle.is-3[data-search-target="result"]
      |  Payments/Billing/Contracts 
    ul
      li
        |  Manual Billing and contractual options please contact 
        a[href="mailto:billing@groupsite.com"]
          | billing@groupsite.com 
      li[data-search-target="result"]
        |  Online payments can be done by doing the following once logged in as manager. 
        ol
          li
            |  Click 
            b
              | "Group Settings"
          li
            |  click 
            b
              | "Account/Upgrade"
          li
            |  select a 
            b
              | plan
          li
            |  click 
            b
              | "Add Payment Method"
          li
            |  proceed to enter in the 
            b
              | payment information
            | . Once completed the card will be processed when the free trial runs out. To cancel, contact 
            a[href="mailto:billing@groupsite.com"]
              | billing@groupsite.com
            |  or 
            a[href="mailto:support@groupsite.com"]
              | support@groupsite.com
            | . 
      li[data-search-target="result"]
        |  Updating payment information can be done by the following once logged in as a manager. 
        ol
          li
            |  Click 
            b
              | "Group Settings"
          li
            |  click 
            b
              | "Account/Upgrade"
          |  click 
          b
            | "Manage Your Billing"
          li
            |  To the right of the credit card information click the 
            b
              | "3 horizontal dots"
            | . 
          li
            |  Click 
            b
              | "Make Default"
            | . 
          li
            |  After, you will be able to delete the previous card that was the default payment method. 
    .groupsite_blue.subtitle.is-3[data-search-target="result"]
      |  Cancelling a groupsite subscription 
    .groupsite_blue.subtitle.is-5[data-search-target="result"]
      |  To cancel a groupsite subscription do the following. 
    ul
      li
        |  contact 
        a[href="mailto:support@groupsite.com"]
          | support@groupsite.com
        | , or 
        a[href="mailto:support@groupsite.com"]
          | billing@groupsite.com
        |  to inform them of the cancellation. This will stop any future billing. 
        ul
          li[data-search-target="result"]
            |  Once the billing cycle runs out the group will go into a disabled mode. This will make the group inaccessible. 
          li
            |  If you would like to reactivate the group a manager or owner of the group would need to contact 
            a[href="mailto:support@groupsite.com"]
              | support@groupsite.com
            |  to inform them of the reactivation. This will also require payment information be re-established. 
          li
            |  Group managers are responsible for the deletion of data, including the removal of members before the group is cancelled. 
    
